results.name: Court Borough Low 2 Black University Red (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Court Borough Low 2 GS ‘Bred’ applies an iconic color scheme to a low-top silhouette inspired by vintage hoops shoes from the ‘80s. The all-leather upper features a black base with contrasting red hits on the Swoosh, perforated toe box and webbing pull tab at the heel. Classic Nike branding adorns the heel overlay and woven tongue tag. A final pop of University Red finishes the durable rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Game Royal
results.story: The Nike Dunk High ‘Game Royal’ showcases classic color blocking on a traditional all-leather upper. The two-tone design is reminiscent of the OG ‘Kentucky’ colorway from Nike’s iconic ‘Be True to Your School’ pack from 1985, featuring a lighter shade of royal blue on the sneaker’s signature Swoosh, eyestay and forefoot and heel overlays. A standard Nike woven tag is stitched atop the nylon mesh tongue, supplying added breathability to the high-top build.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Spartan Green
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Michigan State’ delivers a low-top version of the Michigan State Dunk from 2020. Like its predecessor, the shoe features a two-tone all-leather upper rendered in classic ‘Be True to Your School’ color blocking. A stark white finish is contrasted by a dark green Swoosh and matching overlays at the toe and heel. Standard Nike branding hits decorate the heel and nylon tongue. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber outsole, complete with a traction pattern originally developed for the hardwood.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Michigan
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Nike Dunk Low ‘Michigan’ offers a low-top interpretation of one of the silhouette’s original ‘Be True to Your School’ colorways, first released in 1985 and previously retroed in 2020. The all-leather upper is finished in a rich Varsity Maize hue with contrasting Midnight Navy hits on the Swoosh and forefoot and heel overlay. Padded comfort is provided by a low-cut collar and breathable nylon tongue, featuring a woven tag with traditional Nike branding.

results.name: Kobe 6 Protro Playoff Pack White Del Sol
results.story: The Nike Zoom Kobe 6 Protro ‘White Del Sol’ brings back the original ‘POP’ colorway from 2011, updated with refreshed tooling and a sleeker shape. Polyurethane ‘islands’ create a scaly texture on the white and grey upper, fortified with a black molded heel counter and accented with a matching black Swoosh. The Cushlon midsole packs a large and flexible Air Zoom Turbo unit in the forefoot, along with a softer foam compound in the heel. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a snakeskin-inspired traction pattern for maximum grip.

results.name: Nike Kyrie 4 EP Black Turf Orange
Nike Dunk High EMB Lakers
results.story: The Nike Dunk High Premium EMB ‘Lakers’ goes back to its hardwood roots with a familiar color scheme celebrating Los Angeles’ premier NBA franchise. The high-top carries a black textile upper with Court Purple leather overlays and a bright Opti Yellow leather Swoosh. Wrapping around the lateral heel is a raised and embroidered Nike wordmark in a typeface that recalls the logo of the Los Angeles Lakers. ‘Nike Sports Specialties’ is displayed on a retro woven tongue tag.

results.name: PlayStation 5 x PG 5
results.story: The PlayStation 5 x Nike PG 5 continues Paul George’s creative partnership with his favorite gaming brand. The athlete’s fifth signature sneaker takes direct inspiration from the PlayStation 5, featuring a white textile upper with contrasting black and royal blue accents. A PlayStation logo lands on the sneaker’s right tongue, while tonal all-over graphics on the forefoot and heel overlay reflect the symbols found on the DualSense wireless controller. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length Nike Air Strobel, visible through cut-outs in the grippy rubber outsole.

Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W)
results.story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low ‘Photon Dust’ delivers an understated colorway of the performance hoops shoe turned streetwear staple. The low-top carries an all-leather upper finished entirely in neutral white and grey tones. An OG aesthetic is accentuated via traditional branding elements, including a woven Nike tongue tag and embroidered Nike lettering on the heel tab. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a traction pattern that’s nearly identical to another 1985 release, the Air Jordan 1.

results.name: Nike Dunk High AMBUSH Deep Royal
Nike Air Force 1 Low Fresh
results.story: The Nike Air Force 1 '07 LV8 ‘White Bright Crimson’ treats the classic silhouette to a design refresh with eye-catching accents. The upper is constructed from white leather with a metallic iridescent trim outlining the sneaker’s various overlays. Glossy black patent leather is utilized on the Swoosh and heel tab, marked with a standard Nike Air logo in gradient yellow and red coloring. A similar color-fade effect is applied to the lace aglets and raised Air branding on the midsole.

results.name: Nike Air VaporMax Plus Fresh
results.story: The Nike Air VaporMax Plus ‘Black Crimson Yellow’ uses a fiery combination of colors to highlight the hybrid sneaker’s buoyant tooling. A gradient red and yellow blend is applied to the Air-infused VaporMax platform and foam midsole, the latter equipped with the familiar whale tail-inspired shank from the Air Max Plus. A contrasting solid black finish is used on the upper, featuring a distinctive TPU cage and a red mini-Swoosh for a contrasting pop of color.

Nike SB Dunk High TV Signal
results.story: The Nike Dunk High SB ‘TV Signal’ draws inspiration from a bygone time when skate videos were recorded on VHS tapes and viewed on analog TVs. The high-top features a white leather base with contrasting black suede overlays and a matching black Swoosh in glossy patent leather. A lenticular multicolor print enlivens the quarter panel and collar, mimicking a failed signal on a vintage CRT television set. The scrambled motif is repeated on the sockliner, featuring a Zoom Air unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Nike Cosmic Unity Ghost
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity ‘Ghost’ delivers a sleek colorway of a performance hoops shoe tasked with extending the brand’s ‘Move to Zero’ initiative. At least 25% recycled content goes into the composition of the futuristically styled upper, which encompasses the black cable yarn build, woven laces, and even the marbled blue Swoosh. A matching black finish is applied to the Crater Foam midsole, which works in tandem with a Zoom Air strobel to deliver springy cushioning and on-court responsiveness.

results.name: Cosmic Unity EP 'Ghost'
results.story: The Nike Cosmic Unity EP ‘Ghost’ updates the performance hoops shoe with a mostly black finish. The neutral palette is applied to the recycled cable yarn upper and Crater Foam midsole, which incorporates 10% Nike Grind Rubber. Nike’s sustainability efforts extend to the sneaker’s aesthetic and performance details, including the marbled blue Swoosh and full-length Zoom Air Strobel, both of which are partially composed of recycled content. This EP edition features an extra-durable rubber outsole for made for outdoor use.

results.name: Wmns Waffle One 'Fuchsia Gold'
results.story: The Nike women’s Waffle One ‘Fuchsia Gold’ showcases vibrant hues on a retro-inspired silhouette that carries on the legacy of the iconic waffle franchise. The ventilated upper pairs transparent mesh with contrasting suede overlays in lavender and orange. The latter hue is repeated on the leather Swoosh and TPU heel clip, featuring an angled topline that merges with the wedge-shaped foam midsole. Underfoot, Nike’s waffle traction rubber outsole provides optimal grip.

results.name: Wmns Waffle One 'Black White'
results.story: The Nike women’s Waffle One ‘Black White’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of the lifestyle runner that seamlessly blends old and new. Similar to the DBreak-Type, the upper is constructed from transparent mesh with suede overlays at the toe and heel. The all-black finish is disrupted by a white leather Swoosh and matching branding elements atop the molded tongue. A pronounced TPU heel clip is integrated into the dual-stacked foam midsole, rendered in a classic wedge shape and supported by a waffle-traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Force 1 Crater Flyknit 'Black Chambray Blue'
LeBron 18 'Black White Gum'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 ‘Black White Gum’ delivers an essential colorway of LeBron James’ 18th signature shoe. A solid black finish is applied to the Knitposite 2.0 upper, featuring integrated lacing and a contrasting white TPU heel counter covered in speckled detailing. The sneaker’s innovative cushioning setup features Cushlon foam and full-length Zoom Air that’s partially housed within a large-volume Max Air unit nestled in the heel. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole uses a grid-like traction pattern for maximum grip.

results.name: Waffle One 'Electric Green'
results.story: The Nike Waffle One ‘Electric Green’ applies a lush hue to a lifestyle silhouette inspired by the Swoosh’s running heritage. Breathable comfort is provided by a semi-translucent mesh upper, accented with a black leather Swoosh and bolstered by tonal suede overlays at the toe and heel. A thin, low-cut collar allows for flexibility and a full range of motion, while a TPU heel clip delivers rearfoot stability. Springy cushioning comes courtesy of a Phylon midsole, rendered in a classic wedge shape and reinforced by Nike’s iconic waffle outsole.

results.name: Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame
results.story: The Undefeated x Nike Zoom Kobe 5 Protro ‘Hall of Fame’ celebrates Kobe Bryant’s induction into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame. As a nod to the Mamba’s championship pedigree, a metallic gold finish coats the upper, crafted from breathable mesh with snakeskin-textured leather overlays. Each shoe is accented with a purple Swoosh on the right side panel and a mismatched pink Swoosh on the left. Specific to the left shoe, the pink Swoosh is inscribed with the numbers 24, 10 and 8, representing the jersey numbers that Kobe wore with the Lakers and Team USA. Additional mismatched branding lands on the tongue and heel, both featuring Kobe’s personal trademark and Undefeated’s Five Strikes logo.

results.name: Nike Dunk SB Low Stingwater Magic Mushroom
results.story: Developed in partnership with Daniel Kim’s skate brand, the Stingwater x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Magic Mushroom’ makes use of a crimson leather upper with safari-print overlays meant to resemble the surface of a mushroom cap. On the lateral quarter panel, a small jewel Swoosh is joined by an embroidered and partially scrambled ‘Stingwater’ wordmark. Reverse ‘Nike’ branding adorns the heel tab, while the tongue features a zippered stash pocket and a woven interior tag inscribed with ‘Free Your Mind’ in the same inverted lettering. Underfoot, the translucent rubber outsole reveals printed text on each shoe that reads ‘Plant Emoji’ and ‘With Eyes.’

Kyrie 7 EP 'Daybreak'
results.story: The Nike Kyrie 7 EP ‘Daybreak’ features a pale violet mesh upper with a unique flaming Swoosh in red and yellow. Contrasting pastel green accents land on the tongue and midsole, which houses a large forefoot Air Zoom Turbo unit for extra-responsive cushioning in all directions. Additional performance benefits include a padded collar for Achilles support and molded fins integrated into the laces for a lockdown fit. Underfoot, a bright yellow rubber outsole features a 360-degree computer-generated traction pattern for optimal grip.

Daan Van Der Linden x Blazer Court SB 'Baroque Brown'
results.story: Designed in collaboration with the Nike SB team rider, the Daan Van Der Linden x Nike Blazer Court SB ‘Baroque Brown’ gets dressed in a canvas upper inspired by traditional fishing vests. A fish-hook graphic is embroidered on the olive green leather Swoosh, while a custom heel patch displays a rainbow trout alongside Daan Van Der Linden’s name. The low-top is fortified with a tonal ollie patch on the lateral forefoot and mounted atop a contrasting white rubber midsole. Underfoot, a herringbone-tread gum rubber outsole provides optimal grip

results.name: Supreme x Air Max 96 'Metallic Silver'
results.story: Bringing back the cult classic running silhouette, Supreme works with Nike on a trio of Air Max 96 colorways. The 'Metallic Silver' iteration features a polished metallic finish applied to the synthetic leather upper, garlanded with reflective piping and fitted with a series of transparent windows that reveal a red Supreme-branded insole. Additional Supreme branding lands on the mesh tongue and a pebbled leather heel overlay. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a midsole packed with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot.

results.name: Nike Air Max 96 Supreme Camo
results.story: The Supreme x Nike Air Max 96 ‘Camo’ is drawn from a three-piece set that continues a string of Air Max running collaborations that began in 2016 with the AM98. The retro silhouette makes use of a camo-print leather upper with reflective piping and a dual-branded mesh tongue. Transparent windows on the side panels and toe box reveal a crimson sockliner plastered with an oversized Supreme wordmark. A final Supreme logo hit lands on the heel overlay in metallic silver. The sneaker rides on an olive green midsole with visible Max Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel.

results.name: Nike Air Max 96 Supreme Black
results.story: Releasing as part of a three-piece collaboration, the Supreme x Nike Air Max 96 ‘Black’ updates the retro silhouette with a series of transparent windows on the shark-tooth shaped design elements. The rest of the upper is constructed from black leather with reflective piping and a dual-branded mesh tongue. Additional Supreme branding makes its way to the crimson sockliner and a metallic silver plate on the pebbled-leather heel overlay. The retro runner is mounted on a matching black midsole with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot.

results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 ‘Lakers Heritage’ takes inspiration from the NBA franchise’s origins in Minneapolis, Minnesota, the state colloquially known as the ‘Land of 10,000 Lakes.’ The sneaker’s color scheme reflects the early road uniforms of the Minneapolis Lakers, highlighted by a powder blue tongue and a flexible collar in University Gold. Matching yellow accents are interspersed throughout the black KnitPosite 2.0 upper. The sneaker rides on a Cushlon midsole that works in tandem with a full-length Zoom Air unit, which is partially housed within a visible Max Air unit under the heel.

Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Air Carnivore 'Black'
results.story: Debuting at CDG’s Spring/Summer 2021 runway show in Tokyo, the Comme des Garçons Homme Plus x Nike Air Carnivore ‘Black’ brings back the cult-favorite 1993 cross trainer in a monochromatic finish. The retro silhouette’s defining features remain intact, including a high-cut neoprene collar and an adjustable Nike-branded midfoot strap, coated in reflective 3M for added visibility in low-light conditions. The rest of the upper is constructed from breathable mesh with tonal nubuck overlays at the toe and heel, the latter stamped with ‘Comme des Garçons Homme Plus’ in contrasting white lettering.

results.name: Nike LeBron 18 Minneapolis Lakers (GS)
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Nike LeBron 18 GS ‘Lakers Heritage’ celebrates the storied NBA franchise’s beginnings in Minneapolis, Minnesota. In a nod to the Minneapolis Lakers’ early road uniforms, LBJ’s signature shoe showcases contrasting accents in powder blue and University Gold. The latter hue is prominently featured on the flexible collar and throughout the knit upper, which is mounted on a foam midsole with a visible Max Air unit nestled in the heel. ‘James 23’ branding adorns the custom sockliner.

results.name: LeBron 18 EP 'Lakers Heritage'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 EP ‘Lakers Heritage’ features a color scheme that nods to the Minnesota roots of Los Angeles’ marquee NBA franchise. Reflecting the Minneapolis Laker’s road uniforms, LeBron James’ signature shoe makes use of a black Battleknit 2.0 upper flecked with gold fibers. A matching yellow collar is contrasted by a powder blue tongue and Concord-colored translucent heel counter. The lightweight build is placed atop a Cushlon midsole, enhanced with a full-length Zoom Air unit partially contained within a visible Max Air heel unit. This EP version sports an extra-durable rubber outsole made for outdoor courts.

results.name: Kyrie Low 4 EP 'Light Armory Blue'
results.story: The Kyrie Low 4 EP ‘Light Armory Blue’ features a semi-translucent textile upper with embroidered Swoosh branding and a synthetic leather heel tab. TPU fins are integrated into the laces to deliver a lockdown fit, while the low-cut padded collar offers a free range of motion. The sneaker rides on a full-length Cushlon foam midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot. A multicolor finish is applied to the computer-generated outsole, built with extra-durable rubber made for use on outdoor courts.

results.name: Nike Air Raid White Gum
results.story: The Nike Air Raid ‘White Gum’ delivers a summer-ready colorway of the 1992 hoops shoe specifically built for outdoor courts. An instantly recognizable cross-strap design secures an all-white upper constructed from mesh and leather. ‘Air Raid’ is embroidered on the lateral ankle strap, while ‘For Outdoor Use Only’ is embossed on the molded heel panel. The mid-top is mounted on a matching polyurethane midsole, reinforced underfoot by an extra-durable gum rubber outsole.

The latter is achieved by using embroidered Swooshes and efficient overlays, including an orange webbing strap that folds in on itself to create lace loops. The sneaker rides on a powder blue Crater foam midsole with speckled sidewalls that indicate the inclusion of Nike Grind.

A Bright Mango Swoosh is matched by a large-volume Max Air unit under the heel, which works in tandem with a React foam midsole to deliver a blend of lightweight cushioning and on-court responsiveness.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 GS 'Black White'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 GS ‘Black White’ delivers an essential two-tone colorway of the performance runner. The lightweight upper is crafted from ventilated black mesh with a wider toe box and low-cut collar. A set of interior webbing straps are integrated into the laces, offering midfoot lockdown and a personalized fit. The sneaker sits atop a plush foam midsole, featuring an Air Zoom unit under the ball of the foot for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Court Borough Mid 2 GS 'Black Game Royal'
results.story: Offered in big kid sizing, the Nike Court Borough Mid 2 GS ‘Black Game Royal’ features an essential two-tone color scheme on a basketball-inspired sneaker built for playtime. The upper combines easy-to-clean leather and breathable mesh on the collar, equipped with a webbing pull tab and secured with an adjustable hook-and-loop strap for a custom fit. The mid-top is supported by durable cupsole tooling, complete with flex grooves built into the rubber outsole for a natural stride.

results.name: Air Force 1 Low GS 'Patriots'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Air Force 1 Low GS ‘Patriots’ gets dressed in a familiar color combination that recalls New England’s NFL franchise. The retro low-top utilizes a white tumbled leather upper with a cut-out navy Swoosh and red mini-Swooshes embroidered on the vamp and lateral forefoot. Additional branding hits land on an elongated woven tongue tag and an added pull tab at the heel. The sneaker is nestled atop a durable rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide 'Black White'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide ‘Black White’ updates the performance running shoe with a lightweight build that places a premium on comfort and accessibility. Assembled on an accommodating last, the sneaker makes use of a breathable black mesh upper with zippered entry on the medial side. Additionally, no-tie elastic laces are designed to be secured using just one hand. The sneaker is mounted on a React foam midsole with Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot.

results.name: Presto GS 'White Volt'
results.story: Made for big kids, the Nike Presto GS ‘White Volt’ highlights a simplistic color scheme on a comfortable lifestyle runner originally billed as a T-shirt for feet. The lightweight build features a white mesh upper with a tonal midfoot cage and reinforced toe cap. Embroidered on the toe box is black Swoosh and ‘Just Do It’ in Volt lettering across the left and right shoe. Additional pops of Volt land on the heel and midsole, accented with five dots that nod to Nike’s short-lived Alpha Project initiative.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide 'Pure Platinum Chile Red'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase Extra Wide ‘Pure Platinum Chile Red’ delivers a combination of easy access and responsive cushioning. The light grey textile upper features convenient zippered entry on the medial side, along with a no-tie lacing system that can be easily secured with one hand. Integrated webbing straps offer a feeling of lockdown, while a foam tongue alleviates pressure at the top of the foot. The lightweight build is supported by a Nike React midsole, enhanced with springy Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase 'Pure Platinum Chile Red'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 FlyEase ‘Pure Platinum Chile Red’ highlights mostly neutral tones on an easy-access version of the performance running shoe. Signature Swoosh branding in a bold scarlet hue enlivens the light grey mesh upper, featuring zippered entry and a no-tie cord lacing system designed to be secured with only one hand. A wider toe box offers plenty of wiggle room, while a plush foam tongue mitigates pressure on the top of the foot. Lightweight cushioning arrives via full-length Nike React midsole with a Zoom Air unit housed in the forefoot.

results.name: React Live TD 'Light Violet Champagne'
results.story: The Nike React Live TD ‘Light Violet Champagne’ showcases pastel hues on a slip-on sneaker that pairs breathable comfort and a cushioned ride. Elastic no-tie laces secure the upper, constructed from a blend of pink textile and open white mesh. Pull tabs at the tongue and heel allow the shoe be easily slipped on and off. The lightweight build is mounted on a sculpted foam midsole, supported underfoot by a rubber outsole for durable traction.

Varsity Leather GS 'Particle Grey'
results.story: Crafted for big kids, the Nike Varsity Leather GS ‘Particle Grey’ showcases a neutral monochromatic on a versatile everyday running shoe made with durability in mind. Grey leather is utilized on the upper, featuring tonal Swoosh branding and toe box perforations for improved ventilation. A classic Nike logo is pressed into the stitched tag that decorates the breathable mesh tongue. The low-top is mounted on a plush foam midsole, supported by lasting rubber in high-wear areas.

results.name: sacai x VaporWaffle 'Dark Iris'
results.story: Designed in coordination with Chitose Abe’s renowned fashion label, the Sacai x Nike VaporWaffle ‘Dark Iris’ showcases sumptuous hues on a retro-inspired silhouette that blends elements from the classic Pegasus 83 with the modern Vaporfly. The reconstructed upper features a purple nylon base with contrasting burnt orange accents on the leather Swoosh and heel tab, marked with dual Nike and Sacai branding. A second printed Swoosh continues a doubled-up theme applied in more literal fashion to the sneaker’s tongues and laces. A partially split foam midsole is reinforced by Nike’s iconic waffle outsole.

results.name: Air Zoom Pegasus 38 'Black'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Pegasus 38 ‘Black’ showcases a stealthy monochromatic finish that allows the shoe’s performance benefits to come to the fore. They include an engineered mesh upper built on a new last, yielding a wider toe box for improved comfort. Laces are integrated into a series of interior webbing straps for a more personalized fit. A molded Supreme lace jewel in metallic gold is matched by Nike logo hits at the heel tab and woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a Zoom Air unit in the custom sockliner, featuring a crimson surface marked with dual Supreme and Nike SB branding.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Barkroot Brown (2021)

Inside the shoe, dual Supreme and Nike SB branding decorates the red sockliner, featuring a Zoom Air unit in the heel for responsive cushioning.

results.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Supreme Stars Hyper Royal (2021)

A standard Nike wordmark is embroidered in gold lettering on the heel tab, matching the woven tag atop the stuffed textile tongue. A gold Supreme dubrae shines at the bottom of the lace bed. Underfoot, the outsole plate features a mix of conical and chevron-shaped studs for superior grip.

results.name: Wmns Metcon 6 'Football Grey Arctic Punch'
results.story: The Nike women’s Metcon 6 ‘Football Grey Arctic Punch’ uses a delicate pink hue as a display of fortitude. The pastel finish is applied to the training shoe’s rubber outsole, featuring a wide, stable platform and extended coverage that wraps up the sneaker’s sidewalls, a signature attribute of the Metcon line. The upper is built with a lightweight mesh forefoot, reinforced with a durable screen print and offering 18% more breathability than the Metcon 5.

results.name: Tiempo Legend 8 Club MG GS 'Platinum Tint Rage Green'
results.story: The Nike Tiempo Legend 8 Club MG GS ‘Platinum Tint Rage Green’ delivers a simplistic two-tone colorway of a grade-school soccer cleat made for short-grass and artificial surfaces. The streamlined upper combines coated textile with durable synthetic leather, featuring a diamond texture that yields enhanced control for precise shooting, passing and dribbling. Underfoot, a series of green-tipped studs provide optimal stop-and-go traction.

results.name: Air Structure GS 'Black Smoke Grey'
results.story: The Nike Air Structure GS ‘Black Smoke Grey’ brings back the early ‘90s running shoe in a neutral colorway made for big kids. Breathable black mesh is utilized on the upper, reinforced with angular overlays in black nubuck and grey synthetic leather. A white leather Swoosh is matched by molded eyelets and Nike Air branding embroidered on the heel. The midsole is distinguished by an asymmetrical Max Air unit that’s configured differently on the sneaker’s medial and lateral side.

results.name: LeBron 8 PS 'Empire Jade'
results.story: Built for little kids, the Nike LeBron 8 PS ‘Empire Jade’ celebrates the 600th anniversary of Beijing’s Forbidden City, featuring an aged leather upper in a rich scarlet hue. Raw edges are stained yellow, matching LeBron James’ signature lion graphic embossed on the tongue. A contrasting black Swoosh is set farther back, so that its tapered tail extends to a pull tab affixed to the heel. Flywire-infused TPU panels provide lightweight support. The sneaker rides on a full-length Phylon midsole, coated in a pale green hue and reinforced by a matching glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Max 95 Premium 'Crocodile Skin' By You
results.story: Available through the brand’s customization service, the Nike Air Max 95 Premium ‘Crocodile Skin’ By You dresses the sneaker’s layered side panels in croc-embossed leather, featuring an outer layer that eventually wears away to reveal an entirely different hue. The retro runner rides on a standard polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot, and reinforced by a waffled tread rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Max 95 By You
results.story: The Nike Air Max 95 By You is designed through the brand’s customization service and utilizes polished twill textile throughout the upper, accented with contrast Volt stitching that outlines the sneaker’s layered side panels. Rope laces are looped through webbing eyelets, partially concealed by a breathable mesh overlay. The retro silhouette rides on a lightweight polyurethane midsole, housing visible Max Air units in the heel and forefoot and supported by a waffle traction rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Structure GS 'Grey Fog Lapis'
results.story: The Nike Air Structure GS ‘Grey Fog Lapis’ celebrates the retro running shoe’s 30th anniversary with a simplistic color scheme made for big kids. The silhouette is heralded for its stable ride and distinctive lines, formed with black nubuck and grey leather overlays stitched atop a breathable white mesh base. Deep blue accents make their way to the sneaker’s molded eyelets, signature Swoosh and embroidered Nike Air branding on the heel. Performance benefits include a stabilizing heel counter and visible Max Air cushioning.

results.name: LeBron 8 TD 'Empire Jade'
results.story: The Nike LeBron 8 TD ‘Empire Jade’ delivers a scaled-down version of LeBron James’ eighth signature shoe, featuring a distinctive palette inspired by Beijing’s Forbidden City. A distressed finish is applied to the scarlet synthetic leather upper, secured with an adjustable midfoot strap for a custom fit. LeBron’s signature lion crest adorns the tongue, while a contrasting black Swoosh decorates the sneaker’s lateral side. Underfoot, a rubber outsole in Cucumber Calm provides grippy traction for little feet.

results.name: Phantom GT Club MG GS 'Photo Blue'
results.story: Built for big kids, the Nike Phantom GT Club MG GS ‘Photo Blue’ applies a vibrant finish to a soccer cleat made for both natural and synthetic surfaces. Off-center lacing on the synthetic leather upper yields a clean strike zone, while a grippy texture provides enhanced ball control when shooting, dribbling and passing. Underfoot, the multiground plate is equipped with neon green studs that provide grippy traction for quick acceleration and abrupt changes in movement.

results.name: Nike Blazer Mid READYMADE White
results.story: The READYMADE x Nike Blazer Mid ‘White Camo’ showcases a deconstructed build in keeping with the Japanese brand’s upcycled aesthetic. A half-stitched Swoosh, reconfigured with a pronounced curve and thinner shape, adorns an upper built with splotched foam and irregular side panels in a crisp white finish. More exposed foam tongue is utilized on the collar and tongue, the latter overlaid with three distinct sets of laces. The mid-top sits on a molded rubber midsole that gives way to a herringbone rubber outsole made in part with Nike Grind. READYMADE branding decorates the heel overlay and custom sockliner.

results.name: Tiempo Legend 8 Pro FG 'Black Siren Red Photo Blue'
results.story: A firm-ground performance soccer cleat, the Nike Tiempo Legend 8 Pro FG ‘Black Siren Red Photo Blue’ makes use of coated textile and premium calfskin leather on the upper. The latter material features seamless construction with a molded diamond texture for enhanced ball control. Soft microfiber lines the heel for non-slip comfort, while a molded sockliner provides lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, chevron and conical studs combine for multidirectional traction.

results.name: Wmns Free RN 5.0 By You

results.name: Nike Air VaporMax Plus City Special Atlanta

When open, a bi-stable hinge props up the back of the insole at an angle that allows the foot to intuitively slide in and press down, collapsing the two-piece midsole and locking it in place. A rubber midsole tensioner extends from the toe and around the back of the heel, working in concert with the paten-pending hinge to keep the sneaker secure in both its open and closed states.

When the hinge is open, the back of the insole is raised in the air at a roughly 30-degree angle, allowing the foot to easily slip on and collapse the hinge. To take off the shoe, the wearer steps on the ‘kickstand’ heel and simply steps out.
